{"lemma":"حُلَّةٍ","slug":"حُلَّةٍ","root":"ح.ل.ل","root_slug":"ح-ل-ل","root_link":"/words/roots/ح-ل-ل","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":4,"pos_tags":["noun"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":5},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n8747","n8748","n8749"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%AD%D9%8F%D9%84%D9%8E%D9%91%D8%A9%D9%8D"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"suit, costume, attire"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"mode of doing حَلّ (ḥall) or حُلُول (ḥulūl)"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"alighting-place, collection of tents, douar, settlement, village","tags":["Mauritania","Nigeria"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"cooking pot, especially made of copper","tags":["Egypt"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"large basket or food bin, especially used to store wheat or cereal grains during travel","tags":["Iraq"]}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Borrowed from Classical Syriac ܚܠܐ (ḥellā, “dust, secretion, powdery film; veil”) stemming from the sense of a veil clouding or covering the eyes like dust or a film.\n\nFrom Aramaic חַלְּתָא / ܚܲܠܬ݂ܵܐ (ḥalləṯā, “basket; bucket”), from which Neo-Babylonian 𒄬𒆷𒌓 (ḫallatu, “wicker basket”) is likely also derived. Traditionally however it has been connected with ح ل ل (ḥ l l) in the sense of alighting, stopping, or unpacking for camp; thought as a device so named for its use at a campsite."},"ipa":null,"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n8747","headword_ar":"حّلَّةٌ","root":"Hl","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maHal~N","text_ar":"مَحَلٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":".       -A2-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A large basket,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a thing of the form of a large basket,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Sgh, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of reeds,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"canes,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Sgh, K, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in which wheat is put:"},{"kind":"text","text":"so in the conventional language of the people of Baghdád: (Sgh, TA:) but in that of Egypt,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a copper cooking-pot:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) [pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HilalN","text_ar":"حِلَلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":".]       -A3-  The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"direction"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jihap","text_ar":"جِهَة"},{"kind":"text","text":", and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qaSod","text_ar":"قَصْد"},{"kind":"text","text":",) of a thing; as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hil~apN","text_ar":"حِلَّةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (K:) as when you say"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hl~apa Algawori","text_ar":"حلَّةَ الغَوْرِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in the direction of the Ghowr;"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qaSodahu","text_ar":"قَصْدَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (Sb, TA.)       -A4-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fiyhi Hal~apN","text_ar":"فِيهِ حَلَّةٌ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"In him is weakness,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"languor;"},{"kind":"text","text":"as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hil~apN","text_ar":"حِلَّةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":". (M.)"}],"source_refs":["K","Sgh","TA"]},{"entry_id":"n8748","headword_ar":"حُلَّةٌ","root":"Hl","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A dress consisting of"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"an"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_izaAr","text_ar":"اـِزَار"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a waist-wrapper"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and a"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ridaA='","text_ar":"رِدَا=ء"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"wrapper for the whole body"},{"kind":"text","text":"], (S, M, Mgh, K,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"burod","text_ar":"بُرْد"},{"kind":"text","text":"[which is"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"another kind of wrapper for the whole body"},{"kind":"text","text":"], or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"some other garment:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K:) only applied to"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a dress consisting of two garments"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, M, Nh, Msb, K)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of one kind:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Nh, Msb:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"either of the two garments by itself:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ridaA='","text_ar":"رِدَا=ء"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and a shirt, completed by a turban;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a good garment;"},{"kind":"text","text":"but not so called when upon a man; for in this case it means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"two garments,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"three:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"any good new garment that is worn, thick"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"coarse,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"fine"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"thin:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a lined garment:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K:) but with the Arabs of the desert it means ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a dress consisting of"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"three garments,"},{"kind":"text","text":"i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a shirt and an"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_izaAr","text_ar":"اـِزَار"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and a"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ridaA='","text_ar":"رِدَا=ء"},{"kind":"text","text":": (TA:) pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HulalN","text_ar":"حُلَلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb) [and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HilaAlN","text_ar":"حِلَالٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", as below]: accord. to A'Obeyd,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HulalN","text_ar":"حُلَلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"means"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"buruwd","text_ar":"بُرُود"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of El-Yemen,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"from various places;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and a garment of this kind is asserted to be meant in a trad. in which it is said that the best kind of grave-clothing is the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hul~ap","text_ar":"حُلَّة"},{"kind":"text","text":": it is also said that"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HulalN","text_ar":"حُلَلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is applied to the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wa$oY","text_ar":"وَشْى"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hibar","text_ar":"حِبَر"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xaz~","text_ar":"خَزّ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qaz~","text_ar":"قَزّ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"quwhiY~","text_ar":"قُوهِىّ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"marowiY~","text_ar":"مَرْوِىّ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hariyr","text_ar":"حَرِير"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.) ―         -b2-  Also (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A weapon,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"weapons:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Sgh, K:) pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HulalN","text_ar":"حُلَلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HilaAlN","text_ar":"حِلَالٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (K.) You say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"labisa Hul~atahu","text_ar":"لَبِسَ حُلَّتَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He wore,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"put on, his weapon,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"weapons."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Sgh, TA.) ―         -b3-  Also [like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_izaArN","text_ar":"اـِزَارٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"] (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A wife."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.)"}],"source_refs":["S","M","Mgh","K","Nh","Msb","TA","Sgh"]},{"entry_id":"n8749","headword_ar":"حِلَّةٌ","root":"Hl","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A mode,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"manner, of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Huluwl","text_ar":"حُلُول"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"alighting, taking up one's abode, lodging,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"settling"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (K.) ―         -b2-  See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HaAl~N","text_ar":"حَالٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in three places. ―         -b3-  And see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maHal~N","text_ar":"مَحَلٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in two places. ―         -b4-  Also (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A collection of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"buyuwt","text_ar":"بُيُوت"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"tents,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"houses,"},{"kind":"text","text":"] (Msb, K)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of men;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K;) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maHal~apN","text_ar":"مَحَلَّةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (Har p. 333:) or (K)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a hundred thereof,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb, K,) and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"more:"},{"kind":"text","text":"pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HilaAlN","text_ar":"حِلَالٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (Msb.) ―         -b5-  (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A sitting-place,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"people thereof;"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},